wledge and their development as competent professionals? By considering these and other concerns, this handbook aims to help instructors increase student success and satisfaction, which, the authors hope, will ultimately produce the best possible patient care.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aComputer-assisted instruction. 0aDistance education. 0aInternet in education. 0aMedical educationxComputer-assisted instruction. 0aMedical education. 0aMedicinexComputer-assisted instruction. 0aMedicinexStudy and teaching. 0aWeb-based instruction. 7aEDUCATION / Distance, Open & Online Education.2bisacsh  ahealth.  aonline education.  aprofessionals.1 aPark, Caroline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPerry, Beth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356661/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles